            "title": "Autoritarismo, fascismo e educa\u00e7\u00e3o : ainda a prem\u00eancia de que Auschwitz n\u00e3o se repita",
            "abstract": [
                "A extrema relev\u00e2ncia e atualidade deste livro [...] se torna evidente quando consideramos a advert\u00eancia de Theodor Adorno sobre a persist\u00eancia das condi\u00e7\u00f5es objetivas geradoras do fascismo, mesmo no interior de sociedades democr\u00e1ticas. [...] O leitor n\u00e3o ter\u00e1 dificuldade em reconhecer a extrema atualidade deste livro[...], pois sua reflex\u00e3o repercute problemas que n\u00e3o fazem parte de um passado hist\u00f3rico superado, mas reverberam na sociedade brasileira atual, sob o impulso da cat\u00e1strofe \u00e9tica e social representada pelo bolsonarismo recente. \u00c9 relevante notar que o in\u00edcio da pesquisa de doutorado que originou a presente obra, data do ano de 2017, \u00e9poca em que o ovo da serpente estava sendo lentamente gestado, trans- parecendo na mentalidade moralmente perniciosa do movimento \u201cEscola sem partido\u201d. [...] Um dos grandes m\u00e9ritos da reflex\u00e3o exposta neste livro consiste em desmistificar a repulsa p\u00fablica pela esfera da pol\u00edtica, que em si mesma integra o conjunto de sintomas da s\u00edndrome fascista. Ao contr\u00e1rio da mentalidade de recusa da pol\u00edtica, o autor real\u00e7a a urg\u00eancia de uma politiza\u00e7\u00e3o aut\u00eantica e aut\u00f4noma da esfera do poder, para que se torne poss\u00edvel um exerc\u00edcio p\u00fablico potencialmente resistente \u00e0 dissemina\u00e7\u00e3o da barb\u00e1rie. [...] Hannah Arendt [...] nos lembra que \u201cpol\u00edtica\u201d \u00e9 a esfera do debate p\u00fablico entre diferentes, movido pela perspectiva de um mundo comum. A verdadeira pol\u00edtica se traduz no exerc\u00edcio da liberdade potencialmente voltada para o rompimento do estado de exce\u00e7\u00e3o que na realidade atual silencia o debate p\u00fablico e massacra todos aqueles que representam a diferen\u00e7a. [...] O fascista [...] n\u00e3o deseja conservar nada, pois seu desejo, reprimido, ou muitas vezes declarado, se dirige \u00e0 destrui\u00e7\u00e3o de tudo aquilo que for poss\u00edvel, desde a vida das pessoas que existem \u00e0 margem da normalidade social, at\u00e9 as pr\u00f3prias institui\u00e7\u00f5es democr\u00e1ticas. [...] Em sintonia com as reflex\u00f5es de Theodor Adorno, Hannah Arendt, e outros pensadores voltados para a cr\u00edtica do fascismo, [...] para entender o que \u00e9 a educa\u00e7\u00e3o, nesta obra, devemos nos afastar dos aspectos instrumentais muito presentes na escola, buscando compreender esse termo como sin\u00f4nimo de forma\u00e7\u00e3o do esp\u00edrito, em sentido contr\u00e1rio \u00e0 barb\u00e1rie. [...] Os leitores que estiverem sintonizados com uma compreens\u00e3o ampla da educa\u00e7\u00e3o, voltada para a desbarbariza\u00e7\u00e3o e pacifica\u00e7\u00e3o da sociedade, e sobretudo dirigida ao combate a todo tipo de preconceito, saber\u00e3o encontrar neste livro uma obra de leitura intelectualmente estimulante, esclarecedora e prazerosa",
                "The extreme relevance and timeliness of this book [...] becomes evident when we consider Theodor Adorno's warning about the persistence of the objective conditions that generate fascism, even within democratic societies. [...] The reader will have no difficulty in recognizing the extreme relevance of this book [...], as its reflection reflects problems that are not part of an overcome historical past, but reverberate in current Brazilian society, under the impetus of the catastrophe ethical and social represented by recent Bolsonarism. It is relevant to note that the beginning of the doctoral research that originated the present work dates from the year 2017, a time when the serpent's egg was being slowly gestated, trans- appearing in the morally pernicious mentality of the \u201cSchool without Party\u201d movement. [...] One of the great merits of the reflection presented in this book is to demystify the public repulsion for the sphere of politics, which in itself integrates the set of fascist syndrome symptoms. Contrary to the mentality of refusing politics, the author emphasizes the urgency of an authentic and autonomous politicization of the sphere of power, so that a potentially public exercise becomes possible. resistant to the spread of barbarism. [...] Hannah Arendt [...] reminds us that \u201cpolitics\u201d is the sphere of public debate between different people, moved by the perspective of a common world. True politics translates into the exercise of freedom potentially aimed at breaking the state of exception that currently silences public debate and massacres all those who represent difference. [...] The fascist [...] does not want to conserve anything, because his desire, repressed, or often declared, is aimed at the destruction of everything that is possible, from the lives of people who exist on the margins of normality. to the democratic institutions themselves. [...] In tune with the reflections of Theodor Adorno, Hannah Arendt, and other thinkers focused on the critique of fascism, [...] to understand what education is, in this work, we must move away from the very instrumental aspects present at school, seeking to understand this term as synonymous with the formation of the spirit, in the opposite sense to barbarism. [...] Readers who are in tune with a broad understanding of education, aimed at de-barbarization and pacification of society, and above all aimed at combating all types of prejudice, will know how to find in this book an intellectually stimulating, enlightening and readable work. pleasurable"
